lego:evidence  a  owl:AnnotationProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4033  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1C-F: WT neurons (black bars) showed robust DCV fusion after the first AP burst while fusion in SNAP-25 KO (red bars) neurons was strongly impaired. The blue bars represent stimulation (16×50AP@50Hz).\nFigure 1H: The DCV fusion probability, defined as the number of fusion events/total DCV number per cell, was strongly reduced in SNAP-25 KO neurons compared to WT.\nFigure 2 D-K: The significant reduction in DCV number and fusion probability is seen only at DIV4.\n\nFigure 4 A, C-D: Lentiviral expression of SNAP-25 in SNAP-25 KO neurons fully rescued DCV fusion capacity with a similar number of fusion events and a fusion probability as that in WT neurons.\nFigure 4E: The DCV fusion rate (number of fusion events over time) was similar between WT and SNAP-25 KO neurons expressing SNAP-25.. Experimental description: SNAP-25 KO embryos were obtained by cesarean section of time-mated SNAP-25 heterozygous mice (Washbourne et al., 2002).\nSNAP-25 isoform b was used for rescue experiments and was generated from a mouse brain cDNA library (Invitrogen) using standard PCR techniques and sequence-verified." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2916-7616" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4033" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

